title: For server-to-server communication
description:
This user has API only access and is meant for communicating securely with Directus from your frontend.

This user has elevated permissions over the Public to:
- Submit Forms 
- Upload Files 

From a security perspective, you would typically not want to allow public access to upload files or submit forms.

- Generate a static token access below and include it in API calls to Directus when submitting forms or uploading files from a form.
- Be careful to only use the token server side to prevent the static access token from being exposed to the client side.
